name: "fixed" fixed axel yoyo
description:
Fixed is deathrays first go at a yoyo.. its going to be a sirese of mad Joes favorite yoyos bootlegged but with a twist , since mad Joe is an old school guy he is turning some of his favorite bearing yoyos in to fixed axel yoyos just for the##fixedfriday lovers  ... Expect the same awesome finish that you would get on the deathrays but on a yoyo . Hand cast resin hand made everything down to the cut wood axles . the first run is limited to only 10 yoyos 5 artic blue and 5 red shadow . at least till next Friday  

some yoyo specs 

Diameter: 	55.25 mm / 2.18 inches
Width: 	43.5 mm / 1.71 inches
Weight: 	47.2 grams
Bearing Size: 	Size C center tracked  wood and resin solid spacer "all so comes with 2 wood axels oak and pine  and a screw in axel  
Response: 	CBC "Slim Pad"  slot filled with "death grip putty"

name: DEATHRAY  SPLAT III
description:
THE SPLAT IS BACK!!! it the 3rd of its kind and this time its got a sick color combo, the ken is a 6th gen deathray with reinforced OAK core in white "GLOW IN THE DARK" with hot pink splatter on it and the tama is cast in our famous X-7 doom rainbow finish with pink splatter all over it as well, with a heavy duty vinyl deathry logo sticker on it .

specs info :
 
like always the deathray tamas are made of heavy duty resin that can take a beating and still look sick ... the resin is cast in the color of the tama so you get no chipping or dings on the top surface  . .
and as an added feature the ken comes with the legendary "DEATH GRIP" on the cups for that lil bit of extra grip for the super tech tricks. Also included is the deathray skull bead
